==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cundurango
<hw>Cun`du*ran"go</hw> <pr>(k?n`d?-r?n"g?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The bark of a South American vine (<spn>Gonolobus
Condurango</spn>) of the Milkweed family. It has been supposed, but
erroneously, to be a cure for cancer.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>condurango</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cuneal</ent>⟦br⟧
